## Third-party data sources

The canonical data model derives attestations from third-party primary and
secondary sources. Each `Source` registry entry preserves the bibliographic
attribution of the original source. Where third-party data is re-used:

- **DİA (İslam Ansiklopedisi):** facts and bibliographic information cited under
  fair use / quotation doctrine; direct text not reproduced.
- **Brill Encyclopedia of Islam (EI-1):** metadata only; full-text not
  redistributed.
- **Yâkût's Muʿcam al-Buldān, Ziriklî's al-Aʿlām, etc.:** public domain (authors
  died >70 years ago).
- **Bosworth, *The New Islamic Dynasties* (Edinburgh Univ Press, 2004):**
  dynasty taxonomy and identifiers adapted with citation; narrative text not
  reproduced.

Users of the canonical dataset remain responsible for complying with the
licensing of original sources when re-using derived data.
